Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Jury trial scheduled for January 3, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Marquise Lamar Jackson in court (via zoom) with attorney Jason Daniel Baltz (in person).  Defendant Marquise Lamar Jackson in custody.
